<span class="displaytext"><b>governor (candidate full) <br/> nbc's "today" <br/> august 13, 2007 </b><p><u>governor (candidate last) on the importance of ames:</u> </p><p>nbc's meredith vieira: "and governor (candidate last), good morning to you sir." </p><p><b>governor (candidate full):</b> "good morning meredith." </p><p><b>vieira:</b> "happy guy this morning. you won the straw poll. you invested a lot of time and money in iowa. how important is this victory to your overall campaign?" </p><p><b>governor (candidate last):</b> "well, there's no question it sends a message that america is ready for a change and that change began in iowa. i was delighted to do so well. i know everybody else is wishing they could be in my spot, but i'm glad i've got it." </p><p><b>vieira:</b> "well, you know there are critics who are saying this morning that you basically bought that win and you competed against a weakened field of candidates because (candidate last) and (candidate last) didn't even run. what do you say to those people? do you think the win is diminished by their absence?" </p><p><b>governor (candidate last):</b> "no, absolutely not. as a matter of fact, i had two wins in iowa. the first win was doing so well in building such a strong organization that both (candidate last) and (candidate last) recognized they couldn't win so they pulled out to avoid the visible loss. and then i had another chance to run against a large field and i think i beat the next two combined. so i'm pretty pleased with what we were able to accomplish. we have a great ground team; a message which is connecting. all of the attacks that come my way have been pushed back. i'm hopeful that this gets me a strong position to begin this nationwide effort." </p><p><em>to watch governor (candidate last)'s interview, please see:</em> <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dx8vihhpjk8">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dx8vihhpjk8</a></p></span>



